-- New Zealand Sets India 261 to Win Second Cricket Test, Series
-- B y   D a n   B a y n e s
-- 2012-09-03T04:33:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-03/new-zealand-sets-india-261-to-win-second-cricket-test-series.html
New Zealand  set India a target of
261 to win their second cricket Test in Bangalore as the home
team seeks to secure a 2-0 victory in the two-match contest.  New Zealand added 16 runs to its overnight second-innings
score of 232-9 on day four before  Zaheer Khan  had Jeetan Patel
given out caught behind for 22. India spinner Ravi Ashwin
finished with 5-69, his third five-wicket haul of the series.  India won the first Test at Hyderabad by an innings and 115
runs.  The teams also are scheduled to play two Twenty20
internationals on Sept. 8 and 11.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Baynes at 
 dbaynes@bloomberg.net  